collidesWith

public boolean collidesWith(GameEntity entity)
This method check the collision between itself and another entity. GameEngine calls this method for each entity and they return a boolean value if collision occurs.

Parameters:
entity - Entity to be collided.
Returns:
If collision occurred.

collidedWith

public abstract void collidedWith(GameEntity entity)
Collision responses will take within Game Entities. GameEngine will check for collisions, but every respective response to collisions will be taken care of in different entities like this: -Bonus Entity:.......collision with Player Entity -Player Entity:......collision with Balloon Entity -Sting Entity:.......collision with Balloon Entity -Obstacle Entity:....collision with Sting Entity -Balloon Entity:.....collision with Obstacle Entity

Parameters:
entity -
